[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In this video, I\'ll show you some creative ways on how you can use Open Art\'s latest VFX tool. I\'ve also created a short film using this VFX tool, so make sure to stay tuned to not miss it. Okay, let\'s get into it. So, Open Art have released their Open Art VFX tool,'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and you can do some crazy things with it. The way it works is that it uses a clever masking technique. So, you can select parts of the video that you want to keep and the other areas that you want to change. So looking on the homepage, if we click on open art VFX'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here, you\'ll see it\'s broken up into three categories. So we have replace background, relight video, and VFX. Now you can actually change the background and relight your video using the VFX tab as well, which is where I spend most of'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'my time. You can see some of my examples here on the side. And if you click on templates, they actually have a bunch of ready-made templates here if you want some inspiration. And if you click here, there are even more backgrounds for you to choose from. Then you can upload your'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video footage here. Now, if you\'re shooting in 24 frames per second, you\'ll get around 10 seconds. But if you\'re shooting at 30 frames per second, I think you get around 8 seconds of footage that you can generate. Now, we also get this prompt box down here where'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can add further description on what you want the background to behave like. So, if I click on one of these backgrounds, you\'ll see if I put golden hour beach, it will replace that prompt with a description of that location. And if you want to use your own location,'

[01:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then you can upload an image into here as well. So you could use an image generator that\'s already in Open Art to create your background that you want to be in. And if we go to relight video, this is really interesting. We get loads of different lighting situations that we'

[01:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can change our video to. We got stuff like soft beauty studio, golden hourglow, romantic blush, tense thriller, neon rim light, moonlit blue, and then if we click here again, we can choose from a few more lighting setups.'

[01:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'These are really handy to have as templates as they\'re very varied and can dramatically change the look of your footage. Then going over to the VFX tab, this is where things get really interesting. I do believe it is using'

[01:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Bull AI\'s Switch X technology in the background to drive this new VFX tool which I have used a lot in the past and it is extremely powerful. So let\'s have a look at this video I created where I wanted to test out a few different'

[02:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'things in one video. So once you\'ve uploaded your video then we\'ll come down to this area called areas to keep. Now you\'ll click on select mask. Now it does automatically pick a subject where it\'s masked out the background, but I usually like to do a manual edit. So as you can'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'see, we have this little wand tool down here. And as soon as you click that, it will just pick out a subject in your footage. You can use it again and start clicking around the area and then it will highlight those areas you\'ve'

[02:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'selected. Or we can come down to the custom brush and select the size you want to then manually mask the parts of the video that you want to keep. And then you can use the eraser to remove parts of the mask if you accidentally select more than what you want. So in'

[02:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this example, I\'ve got this footage of me walking with a stick and I\'ve hung up a bit of fabric as I want to interact with it and make it look like it\'s a curtain. When generating the look that you want for your video, we\'ll come to the target look of output. So you get to'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'choose to create with AI or upload your own image. So if we go to create with AI, you can pick which frame of the video that you want to change. I usually just stick to the first frame and then you can describe in the prompt box what'

[03:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you want your shot to look like. And for the image editors, we get a choice from Nano Banana Pro, Nano Banana 2, and GPT image 2. So, I generated this funny image of me wearing wizard outfit and holding a wizard staff and changed the'

[03:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environment to make it look like I\'m in a castle room. And also that bit of fabric I\'ve turned into a kind of red velvet curtain as well. So, with the masking on this video, all I wanted to keep was my face and my hands in the'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shot. And then for the rest of the shot, I want it to be reimagined like the image I gave it. And then you can see a preview of the mask that you\'ve just generated. Then down here, I\'ve added in that image and I\'ve prompted it with'

[03:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video depicts a wizard holding a glowing staff and looking out of a stone window in a candle lit fantasy room. And then I said he touches the curtain just so it knows that when I interact with it, it does start to move the curtain out the'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'way. And this is the video it created. &gt;&gt; What was that? Who goes there? I think that turned out pretty well.'

[04:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s got some nice light coming off that glowing staff. The background looks great. It\'s kept that bit of movement in the original shot. And the hand interacting with the curtain looks great as well. I\'ve been having a lot of fun'

[04:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'using props in my videos as well. So, in this example here, I\'ve got this video of me wearing this very badly designed cardboard wristmounted monitor device thing, and I wanted to see if I could'

[04:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'turn it into some kind of high-tech device with a monitor on it. So, I had this idea of me being lost in the jungle and recording my audio to this monitor. I also wanted to change my outfit and the lighting as well. So, I\'ve got this'

[04:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image that Nano Banana 2 generated, and I think it looks great. It\'s turned the wristmounted monitor into this cool high-tech looking gadget. And I\'ve got some beautiful dappled sunlight coming down on me. And the jungle background'

[05:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'looks really good. And here is the mask selection that I did for that video. So, as you can see, I\'ve only selected my hand and my face to keep. And then the rest I wanted to completely change. And I was really happy with the final video.'

[05:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is log number 23. Still no signs of life, no signal. I\'m going to have to make myself at home here. So, as you can see, when I\'m moving around, you get that really nice'

[05:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dappled light coming through the leaves on me and it\'s moving realistically. And yeah, it just looks really nice. Then, I wanted to switch it and do a night version of this shot. So, I created this image where it looks like I\'m in the'

[05:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'jungle at night and the light from the device is illuminating my face and I think it turned out really well. So, you get that really nice light emitting from the device. I think it\'s just really cool how we can drastically change the same shot with changing the lighting and'

[05:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it just gives it a totally different feeling. For another props test, I actually wanted to see if I could have something that was stuck onto myself. So, in this video here, I actually just made a mushroom made out of Blu-Teack and stuck it to my face. I wanted to see'

[06:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'how well it could create a video where I pulled it off and pretended to eat it to see if it would stay consistent throughout the whole shot. So, I generated this image of me in the forest, and I think it looks great. And here are the parts of the video that I'

[06:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'masked out. Then, in the final video, I think it absolutely nailed it. As you can see, I pull it off. The mushroom still looks like a mushroom as I move it around the scene, and then I take a bite out of it. So, I think it\'s really cool'

[06:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that you can interact with these props as well, and they\'ll stay consistent throughout the shot. I also did some interesting experiments with gaining and losing weight as well. So, I wanted to see if I could add a bit more weight,'

[06:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'maybe have a double chin and change the environment as well. So, I generated this image and here are the parts that I masked out. So, as you can see, I just kept a few select areas of my face. Then the rest I wanted completely changed. As'

[07:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can see, the performance is still there from the original recording. The rest of it moves naturally. I\'ve got that double chin that\'s kind of moving in a very natural way. I was really happy with how this turned out. So,'

[07:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'without adding any prosthetics, I\'ve made myself look like I\'ve added a few pounds. Then, I wanted to go the opposite direction and make myself look gaunt and like I\'ve lost a ton of weight. And I created this pretty'

[07:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shocking image of myself where I\'m just wasting away. I selected similar parts of the face and I think it did an exceptional job. Again, the performance looks great. I think it looks incredibly realistic. It\'s even added a kind of'

[07:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'wider neck to my t-shirt and you can really see in the collar bone and neck area. It\'s really sunken and yeah, it\'s moving in a very realistic way. So yeah, I\'m very very impressed with these'

[07:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'results. Oh, hi there. If you\'re enjoying this video, please consider giving it a like and subscribing to my channel. That would be awesome. You can create some really crazy looking inpainting VFX shots using this tool as'

[08:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'well. So, this first one, I just wanted to change my eye and it was inspired by the District 9 film. It actually moves and blinks naturally with the rest of my face. And this effect here, I wanted it to seem like part of my face was'

[08:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'melting. I was really happy with how it turned out. You can actually see the melted parts moving as I move my head around. And yeah, it\'s a really effective shot. And here are a few more examples.'

[08:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] Now, I want to show you some really unique lighting setups that can really transform your videos. There\'s a lot of really cool lighting tools out there.'

[08:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Like, I\'ve got this handy little flashlight here, and it comes with these small things called goos. And as you can see, it\'s got certain shapes on there. So, when you put it on the front and you shine it through, it will cast that shape of light onto the subject. I'

[08:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really like this effect that it has, but sometimes I\'ve already filmed the footage that I want to add the effect onto and I don\'t want to go back and refilm it. So, that\'s where we can use this VFX tool to add these lighting effects in post. It\'s amazing how these'

[09:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lighting effects can drastically change your shots. Now, I get quite a few comments on people saying that my videos are fun, but the clips I\'m making are too short and you can\'t really do anything with them. Well, I\'m just showcasing what is'

[09:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'possible with these tools, and the best way I find to do that is creating shorter clips to fit as much as I can in a video. And I want to let you know that it is 100% possible to create longer videos with cohesive scenes. So, for'

[09:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'example, you could have a short story with five different scenes, and each scene could be maybe 5 to 10 seconds long. And say you\'ve got a certain environment or effects that you want in each of those scenes to carry through and look consistent and cohesive. All'

[09:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you have to do is make sure that you\'re using an image editor like Nano Banana 2 and use references from previous scenes to then carry on through that look to the next scene. By using this method, you can create long form stories without'

[09:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'having to generate really long individual videos. But you just have to be very smart and make sure that you\'re keeping things consistent between the effects and the look between each scene. So I\'ve made a very short story using'

[10:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'open arts VFX tool to show that you can actually edit together shots and make it feel consistent across different scenes. H transformation plus become a better'

[10:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you. I\'ve never seen anything [music] like this. I don\'t feel so good. Oh. Oh my god. That is crazy.'

[10:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'m pretty happy with how that turned'

[11:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out. So, as you can see, I used a few different effects in that one. Like, I had this small pot of paint and all I did was in the image editor, I changed the label on it and then when I\'m holding it, it has that new label on it. And I had that across different scenes.'

[11:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So it feels like when you see it on the shelf, then you see it in my hands, it\'s all part of that same story. And as long as you do this for each scene, you can make it feel like you\'re telling a longer story and still staying within'

[11:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that same look. And here\'s a video of me testing out the new environment switching app. Environment [music] simulator. It\'s pretty cool.'

